General FAQ

This document is a community driven full breakdown of the respective class. This is a live document where we actively change it based on feedback and changes to the game to provide the best information to the community. The majority of us hang around in the Community Lost Ark Discord in our respective class channels. If you would like to give us feedback or ask questions contact us there.

Why should I play Berserker?

To live out your Guts/Berserk fantasy and yes, even the pain part.
You have 2 viable Class builds, Mayhem or Berserker’s Technique, depending on which playstyle you prefer;

 Be it Mayhem's consistent high uptime Damage or a more bursty playstyle on Berserker’s Technique for some big numbers.
Berserker's Burst comes in the form of an elaborate aura around you which,

in Mayhem’s case, is an amazing black & white glow that is up permanently.

Speaking of glow:

How does my identity work?

Berserker has a meter identity that is filled by hitting the enemy with any one of his attacks, and can be activated once full. While in burst, you are provided with the following effects:

While enraged, you gain 20% Attack and Movement Speed, as well as an 30% Crit Rate increase until the burst ends.  It cannot be canceled.
You gain access to Berserkers greatest Skill,  Bloody Rush (Default keybind Z, also known as BR) which deals significant Damage and has additionally Push Immunity, Weak Point, and Stagger.

After the burst ends, a non-removable exhaustion debuff prevents you from gaining meter from attacks for 30 seconds. This further extends downtime between bursts.

In Lost Ark, Class Engravings further enhance the strengths of the Class and adept its functionalities depending on which one you choose. As for Berserker, both Class Engravings provide excellent build opportunities:  

 Berserker’s Technique (BT) enhances the basic Berserker experience by providing a flat Damage boost while enraged.

The exhausted debuff after bursts does not occur.

This Engraving focuses on maximizing  Bloody Rush’s Damage and is considered the burst Engraving of Berserker, as Specialization increases its Damage even further, while dealing with fewer downtimes in between.

 

 Mayhem fully transforms all aspects of the burst to fit into a playstyle of consistent Damage output:

Berserkers will always start with a full meter and upon enraging, unlock  Dark Rush (Default keybind Z, also known as DR), contrary to  Bloody Rush. It is a very low Damage Skill merely used for its Push Immunity, Weak Point, or Stagger.

Ignoring the burst’s original effects, you only gain 15% Attack and Movement Speed, and half of the Damage the  BT Engraving provides.

While enraged, your maximum health is decreased to 25%, but you gain 70% Damage Reduction, effectively translating to having 83% of your original health.
Your new Health threshold comes with new opportunities in Skill tripods and Engravings alongside Mayhem, which make the penalty worthwhile.

You can end enragement at will by pressing X and recover 25% of your maximum HP, however, you become exhausted for 30 seconds before your identity is reset.

(In 99% of the cases it is NOT recommended to cancel enragement in this manner.)

How do I decide on a build?

Both have their strengths and weaknesses. It’s a matter of personal preference.

Here’s a short summary of the builds. For further information, read their respective sections of this document.

What are my Party Synergies?

Synergies are a buff your party benefits from. These only apply to your party and not the entire raid. Consistent synergies are up for most of the fight while Burst synergies are much more infrequent.

What are the key pieces of my build?

Runes

Mayhem requires as many Galewind Runes as you can fit to properly rotate within the Red Dust window.

Berserker’s Technique players make good use of Wealth Runes and a high Specialization Stat to transform in one skill cycle.

Skill Points

Both Builds require almost every Skill Point Potion available in the game. With up to 6 damage skills, increasing as many of these skills to Level 11/12 as possible proves to be major for your damage.

What is the Red Dust jail?

In this guide, you will notice a lot of references being made to the skill Red Dust,

the “Red Dust window” and cycles/rotations. Being available at Character Level 36, this skill provides you with a 6% Damage synergy for all party members for 16 seconds, at most +24% Attack Power for yourself, as well +33.2% Crit Rate, both for 6 seconds,

 every time you hit any enemy with it. This means

 your dps during those 6 seconds can basically triple for endgame builds.

On the flipside meaning: whenever you miss the enemy, or get interrupted as the skill has no paralysis immunity, your skills are 3 times weaker than what they should be.

This is the trade-off of Red Dust, also dubbed “the Red Dust jail”.

Your main goal for this class is finding the optimal opportunity to use Red Dust and fit in all major skills that you can in the buff window, every 16-24 seconds.

Why is Yearning important?

It’s considered a part of a build despite not being on your character.

Swamp of Yearning is used by supports and gives +8/10/12% Damage and Attack/Move speed to the party. This is a Relic Set they use that has a golden ring.

Mayhem

Written by Swoop, Kamillion

Playstyle

We are always “online”, as in our burst mode is up permanently, and our playstyle revolves around hitting our Skills during the 6 seconds Red Dust window to take advantage of the Crit Rate and Damage increase it provides. Mayhem generally has its Attack and Movement speed capped and can be seen as an easy Class to play.

Stat Allocation

Spec is a completely wasted stat on Mayhem.

In Early Game (ilvl 50-1415) we aim for maximum Crit due to mana issues with Swiftness providing reduced cooldowns.

Most Mayhem players will run Raid Captain due to gaining a free 15% Movement Speed increase from the Mayhem engraving.

As per 1 point into Swiftness, you gain ~0.01717% additional speed.

Therefore:

With a level 2 yearning support and 874 Swiftness you reach maximum speed.

With a level 3 yearning support and 757 Swiftness you reach maximum speed.

Points beyond that may seem useless for more speed,

but contribute further towards reduced Cooldowns.

Here are the Engravings you should aim to use on Mayhem.

Mandatory

Mayhem

+3/8/16% Increased Outgoing Damage. 15% Attack and Movement Speed increased. All incoming Damage -70%.

Healing efficiency is 40%

Shield efficiency is 25%

  • Main Class Engraving, upon burst you are permanently enraged with increased Damage, Move Speed, and Attack Speed at the expense of being at 25% of your max HP and reduced healing.
  • You can leave your identity at any time to recover 25% of your HP but gain a 30 second debuff preventing the re-entry of your identity.

  • This Engraving is perfect for Mayhem due to being capped at 25% max HP, gaining a free Damage Engraving with no downsides at all.

-20% Damage

Cursed Doll

+3/8/16% Attack Power

-25% Healing

  • Due to the nature of Mayhem, the reduced healing effect is almost non-existent
  • This Engraving is NOT additive with Red Dust’s attack power buff; they work fine together.

Level 1 or Level 2

Mayhem

+3/8/16% Increased Outgoing Damage. 15% Attack and Movement Speed increased. All incoming Damage -70%.

In burst mode only 25% of max hp and healing recovery is at 40% efficiency and 25% shields.

  • Has the same damage as Cursed Doll when not using Atropine Potions with no downside
  • Could possibly not be usable in the future due to how Smilegate has treated class lvl 1 builds in the past, making them non-viable in some cases

Cursed Doll

+3/8/16% Attack Power

-25% Healing

  • Best option as lvl 2 for 5x3+2 and an okay option as lvl 1 for 5x3+1
  • No buildup required, unlike Ether Predator

Ether Predator

+0.2/0.3/0.5% Attack Power +0.3/0.6/1% Defense Per

Stack, Max 30 Stacks

  • Provides 6% Damage and 9% defense at max stacks at lvl 1, making it the highest damage option out of all for 5x3+1
  • Takes 4-5 Minutes to reach full stacks and requires restacking if a raid reset/stack duration runs out, losing out on attack power & defense
    (Full stacks = stronger on average than     CD Lv1)
  • In theory the best lvl 2 option as well but the Damage increase does not scale well (9% at full stacks vs 8% flat out from Cursed Doll lvl 2,

buildup not worth it)

Not Recommended

Ambush Master

+5/15/25% Damage to

Back Attacks

  • While the majority of our skills do have a back attack modifier, this does not make this engraving a good option for the majority of players. Reliably landing all your skills in the Red Dust window while also doing back attacks can be quite difficult.

Overdrive and Brave Slash (totaling 30-35% of your damage) do not benefit from back attacks as well.

  • Requires nearly perfect uptime on back attacks and good boss patterns (boss can’t move) to become equal or even out damage the recommended engravings

Mass Increase

+4/10/18% Attack Power

-10% Attack Speed

  • Not recommended due to long animations on Skills and the dependency on the 6 second window provided by Red Dust. 2% extra Attack power means nothing if your 24% Attack power buff runs out before you have landed your skills.

“If you can land your 4 Main Skills inside the Red Dust window, go ahead.”

Adrenaline

+0.3/0.6/1% Attack Power

per Stack

+5/10/15% Crit Rate at

Max (6) Stacks

  • Difficulty in maintaining uptime on Berserker because of long cooldowns and rotation timings.
  • Does not provide much benefits, Berserker has high Crit self-buff Skills in Red Dust/Chain Sword/Mountain Crash, due to this the attack power gain pales in comparison to Cursed Doll or Raid Captain.

FAQ: Mayhem

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord

What is the best 9/7 stone to cut for Mayhem?

Having the best stone that you will not regret upgrading to Ancient is very important for a lot of players, since you will have to commit to one stone eventually

and upgrading a new stone is expensive (6000 Gold per Lvl, 24000 Gold for Lvl 4).

For people that don’t have a 7/7 stone yet and are planning to recut, 

Master’s Tenacity/Raid Captain/Cursed Doll are solid choices for your new stone.

If you happen to cut a 9/7 stone, whereas 7 points are on Raid Captain, you can still use it as lvl 2, being ~.976% weaker than the BiS lvl 2 Cursed Doll and you are better off using Raid Captain over Cursed Doll for the build in the case of a 7/7.

If you already have a good 7/7 stone, feel free to attempt 9/7 with the Master’s Tenacity/Cursed Doll stones for the perfect 5x3+2 build.

Overdrive’s Ruthless vs. Limit Break, which one is stronger?

Over time (based on 3 minutes of Trixion testing), the Combo build is ~7% stronger than the Charged build. However in term of Damage per Rotation, the Charged build is

~7.5% stronger.

Using Ruthless is still recommended for most people due to how easy it is to play.

Can I build “X” engraving?

Refer to the introduction to the Engraving section.

All pros and cons are laid out here. Engravings not listed are irrelevant.

What about Entropy/Ambush Master on Mayhem?

Remember that this combination gives you 65% Crit damage, 22% Damage and 25% Back Attack Damage, all assuming you hit your attacks from the back.

(And +22% Crit rate without any preconditions.)

Of course this also means dropping Nightmare and another engraving, like Master’s Tenacity.

 Overdrive is our highest Dps Skill in the kit and does not benefit from any Back attack increase. That is also true for Brave Slash. Together, they make up 30-35% of your total damage.

 

Assuming these 2 facts, if your uptime on your back attacks is anything but 95%, your effective damage gain from Ambush Master already falls under 16%, weaker than Master’s Tenacity, and Entropy will fall behind Nightmare.

 This is way too much effort to gain damage that Mayhem can get for free by choosing other gear.

 Entropy users are also required to eat food to keep up with the lack of mana, the Crit Damage is diminishing together with Keen Blunt Weapon, and the Crit Rate is wasted as Berserkers already have 80%+ Crit in the late-game.

None of the benefits of Entropy can be well integrated in a class that already is forced to invest all of its points in Crit and Swiftness.

TLDR: If you want to play it, go for it, it’s not my gold. But for the vast majority of players, Entropy Mayhem is NOT recommended.

If you have any question or any input about this feel free to DM us on Discord!

(not.aihie / swoop_/ kamillion)

Is Berserker’s Technique better than Mayhem or Vice Versa?

This is not as simple as it sounds. Both offer at the same time different things and similar things so in the end it comes to your preference and what you value more, be it consistent Damage or more burst Damage and playstyle.

How does Cursed Doll affect Mayhem health-wise?

Some people believe that running Cursed Doll on Mayhem destroys his healing but while Mayhem’s Healing efficiency gets lowered to 40%, his HP threshold falls down to 25%. This dissonance actually gives Mayhem berserkers an advantage to all Healing:

Shoulder Charge?

Shoulder Charge is a relic from old KR builds, serving as a mobility skill with good QoL that can apply bleed and burn through a rune and tripod.
It came from a lack of usable damage skills, which has since been changed with the introduction of Brave Slash. Brave Slash taking up a significant portion of the total damage has rendered Shoulder Charge useless, also taking into account that Berserkers are already at maximum Movement speed.

It can speed up your adventures through Arkesia but it's vastly redundant in Raids.

Berserker's Technique

aka “Brazilian Secret”, “Beer Warrior Secret”

Written by Swoop

Playstyle

Unlike Mayhem, Berserker’s Technique plays somewhat like a transformation Class, where you have to build meter to get in form. However, upon activating form instead of a new set of abilities, you gain a massive stat steroid (30% Crit chance, 20% Attack and Move Speed, and 16%/25%/36% flat Damage gain depending on Engraving level). You also gain access to Bloody Rush, which does a large amount of Damage - unlike Dark Rush which is primarily used for super armor/ stagger on Mayhem.

Stat Allocation

There are 2 different stat spreads you can go on BT:

Spec/Swift is the default option. This helps us cap out Raid Captain and also paired with a lvl9 Bloody Rush cooldown gem allows you to fit 4 casts of Bloody Rush in a burst cycle.

Spec/Crit with a Swift ring is more straightforward, giving you additional Crit rate (yay more yellow numbers). Paired with a Spec/Swift bracelet, you can max out Raid Captain damage.

Gear Set

The Relic Sets we use are Salvation or Hallucination.

Salvation gives additional Damage, and Attack Speed, making this a very good choice for BT. It also has the Take a Break effect, which gives some nice survivability. Can play either stat spread.

Hallucination gives additional Bonus Damage and Crit Rate. This allows you to go Swift as your secondary stat, taking advantage of Raid Captain efficiency easier. Will always play the Spec/Swift stat spread.

Rotation

Berserker’s Technique suffers from skill desync, meaning your rotation will not be the same every time. Overdrive and Finish Strike will always line up with Red Dust, use whatever skill you have off cooldown after that as your third. The other two will go along with Mountain Crash. As long as every Bloody Rush is Crit buffed and you can fit 3 skills into the Red Dust window, you will be set.

Not a rotation, decide in each situation whether you need to stagger fast or not.

Preferably keep high damage skills if you can stagger without them.

FAQ: Berserker’s Technique WIP

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord

Should I play Hallucination or Salvation?

In Trixion testing, the Salvation set was about 1-2% higher in DPS. The damage is close enough between the two though that it comes to personal preference for what you want to play.

Full Spec vs Swift Ring, is there a difference between the two?

Short answer:

Yes, but

only if you have at least a lvl 9 cooldown gem on Bloody Rush, you can fit a 4th

Bloody Rush in your burst mode, which scales better with Spec than Swift.

 No if you don’t have said gem, they both end up with a very similar dps.

Long answer:

It is very complicated to tell which is better per se, as there are many variables that you have to take into account. For our detailed answer we will assume 1595 Spec for the Swift ring setup and 1815 Spec for full Spec setup:

1595 Spec

1815 Spec

  • Fury Meter gain +182.54%
  • Burst Mode Duration +216.77%
  • Bloody Rush Damage +273.81%
  • Awakening Damage +87.16%
  • Fury Meter gain +207.72%
  • Burst Mode Duration +246.67%
  • Bloody Rush Damage +311.58%
  • Awakening Damage +99.18%

For the sake of comparison, we will at first ignore Fury Meter gain and Burst mode Duration and only look at damage difference between the two.

Swift gain:

We assume the ring is max quality, which gives you 200 Swiftness.

This translates into 3.43% AS/MS and 4.29% CDR.

3.43% MS on Raid Captain is 3.43 x .45 = 1.5435% extra dmg, but for CDR it’s very hard to calculate its exact value (since it either allows you to land more skills in the same window or have 0 impact in long windows of invulnerability phases where your skills will come back up with or without extra CDR) so to keep it simple, we will give it an upper ceiling of possible 3.4565% extra dmg, totaling together 5% (for convenience).

Spec gain:

Now we are looking at the full Spec section, you gain 25.719% more BR dmg, and 6.422% more Ult dmg, according to a little over 6 mins parse data I got (all lvl 7 gems and 2 Ults used), BR is doing ~20% of overall dps and Ult is doing ~7.7% of overall dps. To save you all the math stuff, the overall dmg gain from these 2 is ~5.73%.

So what are we getting from this? Full Spec is better?

Not so fast, while full Spec does end up with more raw damage gain, its damage gain is entirely dependent on landing BR and Ult, which means if you are unlucky and not critting (or even hitting) on these 2, Swift ring setup can end up being better since

Raid Captain + CDR do affect all other skills as well.

Okay so assuming if you are unlucky/bad, Swift ring is better?

Well, keep in mind that we are still excluding the extra gain on Fury Meter and longer Burst Mode Duration. Including those, full Spec can feel a bit less punishing to play as it allows for more mistakes in general. For the Swift ring setup, your main damage increase comes from hitting skills earlier than without.

So what is the point of all of these?

The point is that there are people who believe full Spec is only better if you have at least a lvl 9 cd gem for 4th BR.

But both setups offer nearly identical performance without said gem and have their own pros and cons. The difference between the two is the price of accessories and extra AS/MS to increase Raid Captain’s and Mass Increase’s Utility.

Looking ahead, upgrading your BT’s gems means you will have to buy a new accessory if you are using a Swift ring right now, which also has a slightly lower ceiling.

What happened to the Dominion/Awakening Build?

After the recent balance patch in March 2023, the Dominion build is not recommended anymore. The reason for this build was to decrease the amount of time out of Burst Mode that the Salvation set had. With the balance patch, Fury gain was increased substantially, making the reasoning to use Dominion set useless.

Stimulants?

Stimulants used to be vital for a Berserker’s Technique player.

Since the rework in March 2023 enables Berserkers to burst within one good cycle, Stimulants are considered less useful than Atropines. You can still use this to get full gauge before starting the fight and switch back to Atropines.

Can I build “X” engraving?

Refer to the introduction to the Engraving section.

All pros and cons are laid out here. Engravings not listed are irrelevant.

Is Berserker’s Technique better than Mayhem or Vice Versa?

This is not as simple as it sounds. Both offer at the same time different things and similar things so in the end it comes to your preference and what you value more be it consistent Damage or more burst Damage and playstyle.
